Nigerian music duo, Peter and Paul Okoye have hinted on a world tour and fans seem to be excited about this mostly because the music duo had parted ways for over five years only to reconcile in 2021. Paul Okoye, popularly known as Rudeboy, took to his Twitter page on Friday to give this hint. He shared a video of their end of the year concert in 2021 after their public reconciliation went viral. The singer said, “Psquare world tour loading”. ‘Olamide Is My Sponsor’, Portable, Speaks on Journey To Stardom I’ve ‘Resigned’ From Impregnating Women — 2Baba The duo put aside all differences after a five-year separation due to irreconcilable issues. However, to cement their reconciliation, the twin singers held a Christmas concert for their fans to show their comeback. Fans have since been showing their excitement on the announcement, for instance, the Twitter user, @thereal_ebube said, “Didn’t actually know that rudeboy can dance like this, we expecting something hooge from you guys.”(sic) Another user of the platform, @joyce49875397 simply said, “The best duo in Nigeria. I love you guys.” Also, @ibeauchi001 tweeted, “God, I love seeing these two together. May this union last forever, please. Nothing else should ever come up to pull you apart.